# @PROJECT_NAME@

STM32 @STM32_CHIP@ project on stm32-sdk @SDK_VERSION@ — full-stack demo:
MPU6050 IMU + SSD1306 OLED on the same I2C bus, W25Q32 SPI flash logging in
the background.

## SDK rules (must follow)

- CMSIS only, HAL/LL forbidden.
- C++20 (gnu++20), C11 (gnu11).
- MMIO access through `driver::reg::set/clear/write/read/get/modify` only.
- No raw pointers to peripherals — references (`GPIO_TypeDef&`).
- Configs without defaults — every field must be explicit.
- `GpioConfig` is an aggregate; wrap in `gpio({...})` for compile-time validation.
- Trailing comma after the last designated initializer to keep clang-format multi-line.

## Build / flash

```bash
stmtool build --native
stmtool flash
stmtool sdk update          # if [sdk] version = "develop"
```

